## Enumerations

### enum  {#a59b3d3c46e1f1eff571cc1280e8d846c}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum llvm::AliasSet::AccessLattice ">
The kinds of access this alias set models.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="a59b3d3c46e1f1eff571cc1280e8d846ca5f02a99bf7858d28a29400ebad077262" />
<EnumerationListItem name="NoAccess">
 (= 0)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a59b3d3c46e1f1eff571cc1280e8d846ca02c2796b34b99e96c922125bf1336a6e" />
<EnumerationListItem name="RefAccess">
 (= 1)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a59b3d3c46e1f1eff571cc1280e8d846cac66ff35c63941bc9f4f5fdc0fa59e000" />
<EnumerationListItem name="ModAccess">
 (= 2)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a59b3d3c46e1f1eff571cc1280e8d846ca1aab30338607b154f3d0014d04cc9bc1" />
<EnumerationListItem name="ModRefAccess">
 (= RefAccess | ModAccess)
</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

We keep track of whether this alias set merely refers to the locations of memory (and not any particular access), whether it modifies or references the memory, or whether it does both. The lattice goes from &quot;NoAccess&quot; to either RefAccess or ModAccess, then to ModRefAccess as necessary.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/aliassettracker-h/#l00074">74</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/aliassettracker-h">AliasSetTracker.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### enum  {#a8ff56c3bddf5d44f3ef8b81d3abfc3a1}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum llvm::AliasSet::AliasLattice ">
The kind of alias relationship between pointers of the set.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="a8ff56c3bddf5d44f3ef8b81d3abfc3a1a34393e78cce09cfc47ed155aa248907d" />
<EnumerationListItem name="SetMustAlias">
 (= 0)
</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a8ff56c3bddf5d44f3ef8b81d3abfc3a1a321a124cf22e382448a55abe673fed32" />
<EnumerationListItem name="SetMayAlias">
 (= 1)
</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

These represent conservatively correct alias results between any members of the set. We represent these independently of the values of alias results in order to pack it into a single bit. Lattice goes from MustAlias to MayAlias.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/aliassettracker-h/#l00088">88</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/analysis/aliassettracker-h">AliasSetTracker.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
